If you are managing other health conditions as well as your diabetes, this
adds another hurdle to maintaining a healthy balanced diet.
For example, coeliac disease (intolerance to gluten) is more common in people
with Type 1 diabetes as both are autoimmune conditions. We’re here to help you
on your journey to eating well with diabetes and coeliac disease.
Dietitians, experts in food and nutrition, will give you information and
support to help you make changes to your eating pattern, so it’s important to
ask your GP or consultant for a referral.
Someone is diagnosed with diabetes every two minutes. Your donation can change
